meanings.definition: To press or squeeze between two surfaces
meanings.sent1: She was jambing the clothes into the suitcase.
meanings.sent2: He jambing the toothpaste tube to get the last bit out.
meanings.sent3: The cat kept jambing itself into the small box for fun.
meanings.sent4: The traffic was jambing up the narrow street like a clogged drain.
meanings.sent5: The wrestler's opponent tried jambing him against the ropes.

meanings.definition: The act of blocking or obstructing
meanings.sent1: The jambing of the door prevented anyone from entering.
meanings.sent2: The jambing of the road caused a long line of cars.
meanings.sent3: The jambing of the printer led to a paper jam.
meanings.sent4: The jambing of the pipe resulted in a water leak.
meanings.sent5: The jambing of the phone lines disrupted communication.

meanings.definition: A vertical side piece of a doorway or window frame
meanings.sent1: She leaned against the jambing of the door while waiting.
meanings.sent2: The carpenter measured the jambing for the new window.
meanings.sent3: The cat scratched the jambing of the window frame.
meanings.sent4: The ivy climbed up the jambing of the old house.
meanings.sent5: The sunlight streamed through the jambing of the open door.
